io.qsrlabs.nexus.middleware.scxml.handle.title: Build an object ready to be serialized into a SOAP message
help: This handler builds into the session an object that has the correct structure to serialize a SOAP message. It supports SOAP 1.2 and WSDL 1.1

name.help: name of the object in session where payload is generated; this should be used in http client handler

meta.wsdlName.help: meta information, not to be changed by user, containing the name of wsdl

meta.wsdlUrl.help: meta information, not to be changed by user, containing the url of wsdl at time of generation; it will be used at runtime as well, so it must be accessible from http client gw

meta.wsdlBinding.help: meta information, not to be changed by user, containing the binding used from wsdl

meta.wsdlOperation.help: meta information, not to be changed by user, containing the operation used from wsdl

events: returns same events as the one received
io.qsrlabs.nexus.middleware.scxml.handle.label: getSmsDeliveryStatus
